  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nIn my project I'm using a [husky](https://github.com/typicode/husky) git hook to check that all commit messages adhere to [conventional commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0-beta.4/) before they are allowed.\r\n\r\nAfter I run `forge install`, forge fails with the following error in my project:\r\n\r\n```text\r\n⧗   input: forge install: forge-std\r\n✖   subject may not be empty [subject-empty]\r\n✖   type may not be empty [type-empty]\r\n\r\n✖   found 2 problems, 0 warnings\r\nⓘ   Get help: https://github.com/conventional-changelog/commitlint/#what-is-commitlint\r\n\r\nhusky - commit-msg hook exited with code 1 (error)\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt would be helpful to be able to disable this behavior. There should several situations in which users may prefer forge not to auto-created git commits for them - it seems like a sensible thing to do to enable an escape hatch.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
